-- Arab Cotton Ginning Chairman Olama Steps Down; Ahmed Elbosaty Is Successor
-- B y   A h m e d   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2010-10-22T06:29:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-22/arab-cotton-ginning-chairman-olama-steps-down-ahmed-elbosaty-is-successor.html
Arab Cotton Ginning Co., Egypt’s
biggest publicly traded cotton producer, said its chairman of 14
years, Hani Olama, has stepped down.  Olama’s executive role will be filled by newly elected
managing director Ahmed Elbosaty, Olama said at a press
conference yesterday. Olama will remain on the company’s board
as a non-executive director, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Farrand at 
 tfarrand@bloomberg.net  